Monks are disciplined martial artists who turn the body, breath, and
mind into weapons.  They live by restraint: a monk cannot marry, swear
an oath, own boats, or gather wealth like other adventurers.  In return,
they gain a focused path built around chi, bare-handed combat, fighting
styles, and carefully chained techniques.

Chi is the center of the guild.  It fuels monk abilities, strengthens
inner defense, and helps keep combat routes alive.  A monk who manages
chi well can flow from opener to bridge to finisher, building rhythm
instead of simply repeating isolated attacks.

Modern monk combat uses several fighting styles, including tiger,
crane, snake, monkey, and dragon.  Techniques can create combo tags,
carry momentum between styles, and finish a route with a stronger
effect.  Monks also earn notches through training and challenge, and
must prove themselves over a long road toward mastery.

This guild is best suited for players who want a disciplined melee path
with resource management, combo planning, and a strong ascetic theme.
It is not a guild for players who want easy wealth or heavy equipment.

